## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) defines the complete functional and non-functional requirements for **RoyalLagn**, a cross-platform mobile wedding vendor marketplace application. The document is intended for the development team, QA engineers, and project stakeholders. It serves as the contractual baseline between product and engineering.

### 1.2 Scope

**RoyalLagn** is a B2B2C marketplace connecting couples planning weddings with verified local vendors across 14 service categories (Photographers, Venues, Caterers, Decorators, Makeup Artists, Mehndi Artists, DJs, Bridal Wear, Groom Wear, Jewellery & Accessories, Pandits, Invites & Cards, Pre-Wedding Shoot, Music & Dance).

**In scope for this SRS:**
- Customer-facing mobile app (browse, search, favourite, enquire, profile)
- Vendor dashboard (profile management, enquiries, subscriptions)
- Admin dashboard (platform management, vendor approval, payments, subscriptions)
- All backend integrations: Supabase, Cloudinary, Razorpay, MSG91, Expo Push, Resend, Google Maps

**Out of scope:**
- Separate web admin panel (React + Vite, planned Phase 5)
- In-app chat / messaging (Phase 3)
- iOS App Store submission (Phase 5)
- Algolia search migration (Phase 2 trigger: >20,000 vendors)

### 1.3 Definitions, Acronyms & Abbreviations

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| Customer | An end-user browsing the app to discover and contact wedding vendors |
| Vendor | A business offering wedding services, registered and listed on the platform |
| Admin | A RoyalLagn platform operator with full management access |
| Enquiry | A structured contact request submitted by a Customer to a Vendor |
| Subscription | A recurring monthly plan purchased by a Vendor for platform listing |
| Trial | A 14-day free listing period for newly approved Vendors |
| SRS | Software Requirements Specification |
| PRD | Product Requirements Document |
| FR | Functional Requirement |
| NFR | Non-Functional Requirement |
| RLS | Row Level Security (Supabase PostgreSQL) |
| OTP | One-Time Password |
| CDN | Content Delivery Network |
| MRR | Monthly Recurring Revenue |
| EAS | Expo Application Services |
| FCM | Firebase Cloud Messaging |
| UPI | Unified Payments Interface (India) |
| DPDP | Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 (India) |

