## 2. Overall Description

### 2.1 Product Perspective

RoyalLagn is a new product, not a replacement for an existing system. The mobile app is the primary customer and vendor interface. A separate web-based admin panel is planned for Phase 5. The system depends on Supabase as its backend database and auth layer, with Razorpay for payment processing and MSG91 for communication.

**System Context (textual):**

```
[Customer / Vendor / Admin]
        |
[RoyalLagn React Native App — Expo SDK 54]
        |
   +----+--------------------------------------------+
   |                   Supabase                       |
   |   PostgreSQL (RLS)  |  Auth  |  Edge Functions   |
   +----+--------+--------+-------+-------------------+
        |        |        |           |
  [Cloudinary] [Razorpay] [MSG91]  [Expo Push / FCM]
  (media CDN) (payments) (OTP/WA) (push notifications)
```

### 2.2 Product Functions Summary

- **Customers** browse 14 vendor categories, search and filter vendors, view profiles and portfolios, save favourites, and submit enquiries.
- **Vendors** manage their business profile, services, portfolio, pricing, and subscription plan. They receive and respond to customer enquiries.
- **Admins** approve new vendors, manage all vendor accounts and subscriptions, view platform-wide payments and analytics, and moderate content.

### 2.3 User Classes & Characteristics

| User Class | Authentication | Technical Proficiency | Primary Goal |
|-----------|---------------|----------------------|-------------|
| Customer | Phone OTP | Low to Medium (smartphone-literate) | Find and contact wedding vendors |
| Vendor | Email + Password | Medium (small business owner) | Get leads and manage business profile |
| Admin | Email + Password (role-gated) | Medium to High | Maintain platform health and revenue |

### 2.4 Operating Environment

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Mobile Platform | Android (primary), iOS (secondary), Web (Expo) |
| Minimum Android Version | Android 8.0 (API level 26) |
| Minimum iOS Version | iOS 15.1 |
| Framework | Expo SDK 54 / React Native 0.81.5 |
| Architecture | New Architecture enabled (newArchEnabled: true) |
| Network | Requires internet; no offline mode in v1.0 |
| Screen Sizes | 360 dp to 430 dp width; notch/island handled via SafeAreaView |
| Theme | Light mode default; dark mode fully supported via NativeWind v4 |

### 2.5 Design & Implementation Constraints

| ID | Constraint |
|----|-----------|
| C-01 | All routing must use Expo Router v6 file-based routing |
| C-02 | Styling must use NativeWind v4 (Tailwind CSS for React Native); inline StyleSheet is acceptable only where performance requires it |
| C-03 | All payments must be processed exclusively through Razorpay server-side Edge Functions; the mobile client must never hold the Razorpay API secret |
| C-04 | All media uploads must be signed by a Supabase Edge Function before hitting Cloudinary; unsigned uploads must be disabled in the Cloudinary dashboard |
| C-05 | npm installs must use --legacy-peer-deps due to lucide-react-native peer dependency conflict with React 19 |
| C-06 | New Architecture (newArchEnabled: true) must remain enabled; it is required by react-native-reanimated v4 |
| C-07 | The android/ and ios/ native folders are not committed; they are generated via expo prebuild during CI/CD |
| C-08 | Session tokens must be stored using Expo SecureStore; AsyncStorage must not be used for sensitive session data |
| C-09 | Vendor phone numbers must never be exposed in any API response to customers; WhatsApp/call links must be generated server-side post-enquiry |

### 2.6 Assumptions & Dependencies

| ID | Assumption / Dependency |
|----|------------------------|
| A-01 | Supabase project is provisioned and the schema from Section 6 has been applied before any backend-dependent feature is developed |
| A-02 | MSG91 WhatsApp Business API approval takes 2 to 3 weeks; Phase 2 enquiry flows must not block on this |
| A-03 | Razorpay KYC (GST/PAN) completion takes 2 to 3 business days; subscription payments cannot go live until KYC is approved |
| A-04 | All vendor categories are static (14 total); category additions require a code change |
| A-05 | Initial geography is limited to Tier 1 and Tier 2 cities in Maharashtra (Pune, Mumbai, Lonavala, Nashik) |
| A-06 | data/vendorData.ts is a temporary placeholder; it must be replaced with Supabase queries before public launch |
| A-07 | FavoritesContext in-memory state is a temporary placeholder; it must be synced to the Supabase favorites table after auth is implemented |

