## 3. Functional Requirements

Requirements are numbered FR-XXX. Priority is: **P1** (must-have, blocks launch), **P2** (should-have, Phase 2), **P3** (nice-to-have, Phase 3+).

---

### 3.1 Authentication & Session Management

| FR | Description | Priority |
|----|-------------|----------|
| FR-001 | The system shall provide a phone number input screen with a +91 India country code prefix for customer login | P1 |
| FR-002 | The system shall send a 6-digit OTP to the customer's phone number via Supabase Auth with MSG91 fallback | P1 |
| FR-003 | The 6-digit OTP input shall auto-focus each digit field and auto-submit when the 6th digit is entered | P1 |
| FR-004 | The system shall enforce a 30-second cooldown timer before allowing an OTP resend | P1 |
| FR-005 | Supabase shall enforce a maximum of 5 OTP attempts per phone number per hour | P1 |
| FR-006 | Upon successful OTP verification, the system shall check users.role: customer navigates to /(tabs), vendor to /vendor-dashboard, admin to /admin-dashboard | P1 |
| FR-007 | A first-time customer (no existing users row) shall be created with role = 'customer' and navigated to a profile setup screen | P1 |
| FR-008 | Vendor authentication shall use email + password via supabase.auth.signInWithPassword() | P1 |
| FR-009 | Admin authentication shall use email + password; the system shall verify users.role = 'admin' server-side before granting access | P1 |
| FR-010 | Session tokens shall be persisted using Expo SecureStore and automatically restored on app launch (auto-login) | P1 |
| FR-011 | The Forgot Password flow shall send a reset email via Supabase Auth and Resend; the vendor shall see "Check your email for reset instructions" | P1 |
| FR-012 | Logout shall call supabase.auth.signOut(), clear SecureStore, and navigate to /DashboardCenter | P1 |
| FR-013 | Admin accounts shall be created manually in the Supabase dashboard; there shall be no self-registration for admin role | P1 |
| FR-014 | All protected routes (vendor dashboard, admin dashboard, favourites sync, profile) shall redirect unauthenticated users to the login screen | P1 |

