## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Performance

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-001 | The app shall render the Home screen fully (above-the-fold) within 2 seconds on a 4G connection on a mid-range Android device (>=2 GB RAM) |
| NFR-002 | API responses from Supabase for list queries (20 results) shall return within 500 ms under normal load |
| NFR-003 | Vendor card thumbnails shall use Cloudinary auto-transformations (w_400,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto) and shall not exceed 100 KB |
| NFR-004 | List queries shall be cached client-side for 5 minutes using React Query or SWR to avoid redundant network calls on tab re-focus |
| NFR-005 | Search input shall debounce at 300 ms before triggering a server-side query; previous requests shall be cancelled via AbortController |
| NFR-006 | The APK release build size shall not exceed 50 MB |

### 4.2 Scalability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-007 | The database schema and RLS policies shall support at least 50,000 vendor records and 500,000 customer accounts without schema changes |
| NFR-008 | Full-text search shall use PostgreSQL tsvector generated columns; Algolia migration shall be triggered when vendor count exceeds 20,000 |
| NFR-009 | Cloudinary storage and bandwidth shall be monitored; the plan shall be upgraded before the 25 GB free tier is exceeded |
| NFR-010 | Push notifications shall use Expo Push batch API in groups of 100 per Edge Function invocation |

### 4.3 Security

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-011 | All database tables shall have Supabase RLS enabled; the service role key shall only be used inside Edge Functions and never exposed to the client |
| NFR-012 | Vendor phone numbers shall never appear in any client-side API response; they shall only be used server-side to construct WhatsApp/call links after an enquiry is created |
| NFR-013 | Razorpay payment orders shall only be created by Edge Functions using the Razorpay API secret; the secret must not be embedded in the mobile app bundle |
| NFR-014 | Cloudinary upload signatures shall be generated by Edge Functions; unsigned direct uploads shall be disabled in Cloudinary dashboard settings |
| NFR-015 | Razorpay webhook payloads shall be verified using HMAC-SHA256 with the webhook secret |
| NFR-016 | OTP brute-force shall be rate-limited at 5 attempts per phone number per hour via Supabase Auth |
| NFR-017 | Session tokens shall be stored in Expo SecureStore (hardware-backed keystore on Android, Keychain on iOS) |
| NFR-018 | The app shall use HTTPS for all API and CDN requests; plain HTTP connections shall be rejected at the network layer |
| NFR-019 | The app shall comply with OWASP Mobile Top 10 (2024), with particular attention to M1 (Improper Credential Usage), M2 (Inadequate Supply Chain Security), and M8 (Security Misconfiguration) |
| NFR-020 | Personal data (phone number, email, name) shall be handled in compliance with the Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 (DPDP); a Privacy Policy URL shall be linked from the app and Play Store listing |

### 4.4 Availability & Reliability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-021 | The system shall target 99.5% uptime for the Supabase backend (aligned with Supabase Pro SLA) |
| NFR-022 | Supabase Realtime connection drops shall be automatically retried with exponential backoff (max 30-second interval) |
| NFR-023 | Failed push notification deliveries shall be retried up to 3 times with a 1-minute interval before being discarded |
| NFR-024 | The Razorpay webhook handler shall be idempotent; duplicate events must not cause double-processing (enforced via razorpay_payment_id uniqueness check) |
| NFR-025 | Firebase Crashlytics shall be integrated before production launch; target >=99.0% crash-free sessions |

### 4.5 Usability & Accessibility

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-026 | All interactive elements shall have a minimum touch target size of 44 x 44 dp per Apple HIG and Google Material Design guidelines |
| NFR-027 | Colour contrast between text and background shall meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text) in both light and dark mode |
| NFR-028 | All images shall provide accessibilityLabel props for screen reader support |
| NFR-029 | Loading states shall display skeleton placeholder UI rather than blank screens |
| NFR-030 | Error messages shall be displayed inline near the relevant form field and shall be actionable (e.g. "Enter a valid 10-digit mobile number") |
| NFR-031 | The app shall support Indian English (en-IN) as the primary locale; all monetary values shall use the Rs. prefix with Indian number formatting |

### 4.6 Maintainability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-032 | All shared business logic (favourites toggle, enquiry submission, profile completion calculation) shall be extracted into custom hooks or utility functions |
| NFR-033 | TypeScript strict mode shall be enabled; the codebase shall compile with zero TypeScript errors |
| NFR-034 | New screens shall follow the existing file structure: customer screens in app/(tabs)/, vendor screens in app/vendor-*, admin screens in app/admin-* and app/*-admin |
| NFR-035 | Supabase Edge Functions shall be versioned and tested in a staging project before deployment to production |
| NFR-036 | EAS Update shall be configured for over-the-air (OTA) hotfixes; OTA pushes are limited to JavaScript bundle changes only |
| NFR-037 | All hardcoded data in current static data files shall be replaced with live Supabase queries before the v1.0 production release |

### 4.7 Portability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|------------|
| NFR-038 | The app shall build and run without platform-specific code paths for both Android and iOS via Expo managed workflow |
| NFR-039 | The web preview (Expo Web) shall be functionally equivalent to the mobile build for all customer-facing screens; minor layout differences are acceptable |
| NFR-040 | All Supabase Edge Functions shall run on Deno runtime and must not depend on Node.js-only APIs |

---

## 5. System Interface Requirements

### 5.1 Supabase (Backend-as-a-Service)

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | PostgreSQL database, user authentication, Realtime subscriptions, Edge Functions |
| SDK | @supabase/supabase-js v2 |
| Auth Methods | Phone OTP (customers), Email + Password (vendors, admin) |
| Database | PostgreSQL 15+ with Row Level Security on all tables |
| Edge Functions | Deno runtime; deployed to Supabase Edge |
| Realtime | WebSocket subscriptions for: notifications (unread badge), enquiries (vendor inbox), vendors (admin pending count) |
| Credentials | SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in Expo app config (public); SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in Edge Function environment only |
| Failure Behaviour | Client displays "Something went wrong. Please try again."; non-critical operations (view count, analytics) fail silently |

### 5.2 Cloudinary (Media Storage & CDN)

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Vendor portfolio image/video storage, automatic compression and CDN delivery |
| Upload Flow | Client requests a signed upload credential from Supabase Edge Function; client POSTs directly to Cloudinary with the signature |
| Folder Structure | royallagn/vendors/{vendor_id}/portfolio/, .../avatar.jpg, royallagn/users/{user_id}/avatar.jpg, royallagn/banners/ |
| Delivery Transformations | Thumbnail: w_200,h_200,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto | Card: w_400,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto | Hero: w_800,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto |
| Media Limits | Photos: max 10 MB; Videos: max 100 MB (Premium plan only) |
| Deletion | Via Edge Function calling Cloudinary destroy API using cloudinary_id stored in vendor_portfolio |
| Failure Behaviour | Upload failures show a per-image retry button; partial failures do not prevent saving successfully uploaded images |

### 5.3 Razorpay (Payments)

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Vendor subscription billing (recurring), payment tracking |
| Supported Methods | UPI, Credit/Debit Card, Net Banking, Wallets |
| Integration Pattern | Server-side only: app calls Edge Function, Edge Function calls Razorpay API, returns checkout URL/ID to app |
| SDK | react-native-razorpay for in-app checkout; WebView fallback |
| Webhook Endpoint | POST /functions/v1/razorpay-webhook (Supabase Edge Function) |
| Webhook Events | payment.captured, payment.failed, refund.processed, subscription.charged, subscription.cancelled |
| Signature Verification | HMAC-SHA256 using X-Razorpay-Signature header |
| Plan IDs | plan_basic_999 (Rs.999/mo), plan_standard_1999 (Rs.1,999/mo), plan_premium_4999 (Rs.4,999/mo) |
| Idempotency | Webhook handler checks payments.razorpay_payment_id uniqueness before INSERT |

### 5.4 MSG91 (SMS / OTP / WhatsApp)

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | OTP delivery fallback (if Supabase SMS quota exceeded), WhatsApp Business alerts to vendors |
| OTP | Triggered by Supabase Edge Function when Supabase native OTP fails; 6-digit code, valid for 10 minutes |
| WhatsApp | Used to notify vendors of new enquiries; requires Meta WhatsApp Business API approval (2 to 3 weeks) |
| Template Messages | All WhatsApp messages must use pre-approved MSG91 templates (DLT registration required) |
| Failure Behaviour | If WhatsApp delivery fails, the enquiry is still saved; Expo Push is used as fallback notification |

### 5.5 Expo Push Notifications / FCM

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Real-time push notifications to vendor and customer devices |
| Token Storage | Expo push tokens stored in push_tokens table; updated on each app open |
| Delivery | All push sends initiated from Supabase Edge Functions; the mobile client never sends push notifications directly |
| Batch Size | Maximum 100 tokens per Expo Push API batch request |
| FCM | Android background delivery reliability; FCM server key stored in Edge Function environment only |
| Notification Types | New enquiry (vendor), subscription expiring (vendor), payment confirmation (vendor), new vendor pending (admin) |

### 5.6 Resend (Transactional Email)

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Transactional emails: welcome, subscription confirmation, password reset, vendor approval/suspension |
| From Address | noreply@royallagn.in (requires domain DNS configuration) |
| Templates | Welcome Email, Subscription Confirmed, Subscription Expiring, Subscription Expired, Vendor Approved, Vendor Suspended, Password Reset |
| Free Tier | 3,000 emails/month; upgrade required above this threshold |
| Failure Behaviour | Email delivery failures are logged; they do not block the primary database operation |

### 5.7 Google Maps Platform

| Attribute | Specification |
|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Vendor location display, address autocomplete in onboarding, nearby vendor search |
| APIs Used | Geocoding API, Places Autocomplete API, Maps JavaScript API (web) |
| Implementation Phase | Phase 5 (polish); not required for Phase 1 to 4 features |
| Billing | $200/month free credit; monitor usage to stay within credit during initial growth |

---

## 6. Data Requirements

### 6.1 Core Entities

| Entity | Key Attributes |
|--------|---------------|
| users | id (UUID PK), phone (UNIQUE), email (UNIQUE), name, avatar_url, role (customer/vendor/admin), created_at |
| vendors | id, user_id (FK to users), business_name, category, tagline, about, location, city, lat, lng, phone, starting_price, price_level, tags[], rating, review_count, is_verified, is_featured, subscription_plan, subscription_status, profile_views, admin_notes, deleted_at |
| vendor_services | id, vendor_id (FK to vendors), service_name |
| vendor_portfolio | id, vendor_id, cloudinary_url, cloudinary_id, media_type (photo/video), display_order, created_at |
| vendor_packages | id, vendor_id, package_name, price, description, inclusions[] |
| vendor_availability | id, vendor_id, blocked_date (DATE), reason, UNIQUE(vendor_id, blocked_date) |
| favorites | id, customer_id (FK to users), vendor_id (FK to vendors), created_at, UNIQUE(customer_id, vendor_id) |
| enquiries | id, customer_id, vendor_id, customer_name, customer_phone, wedding_date, guest_count, message, status (new/read/replied/closed), vendor_reply, created_at, updated_at |
| bookings | id, customer_id, vendor_id, enquiry_id, event_date, event_location, amount, advance_paid, status (pending/confirmed/advance_paid/completed/cancelled), razorpay_order_id, razorpay_payment_id, cancellation_reason, notes |
| reviews | id, booking_id, customer_id, vendor_id, rating (1-5), comment, is_visible, created_at |
| vendor_subscriptions | id, vendor_id, plan (basic/standard/premium), price, status (active/expired/cancelled/trial), razorpay_subscription_id, razorpay_plan_id, start_date, end_date, trial_end_date, created_at |
| payments | id, type (subscription), reference_id, vendor_id, amount, status (success/failed/refunded/pending), razorpay_payment_id (UNIQUE), razorpay_order_id, refund_id, failure_reason, created_at |
| notifications | id, user_id, title, body, type (enquiry/booking/review/subscription/system), reference_id, action_url, is_read, created_at |
| push_tokens | id, user_id, token, platform (ios/android), created_at, UNIQUE(user_id, token) |

### 6.2 Subscription Plan Features

| Feature | Trial (14 days) | Basic (Rs.999/mo) | Standard (Rs.1,999/mo) | Premium (Rs.4,999/mo) |
|---------|:--------------:|:----------------:|:---------------------:|:--------------------:|
| Enquiries/month | 5 | 10 | Unlimited | Unlimited |
| Portfolio photos | 5 | 10 | 50 | 50 |
| Portfolio videos | No | No | No | Yes |
| Listing priority | Normal | Normal | Priority | Featured (home) |
| Analytics | None | Basic | Standard | Full |
| Support | Email | Email | WhatsApp | Dedicated |

### 6.3 Data Integrity Rules

| Rule | Implementation |
|------|---------------|
| Vendor rating auto-update | PostgreSQL trigger on reviews INSERT/UPDATE recalculates vendors.rating and vendors.review_count |
| vendors.updated_at auto-update | PostgreSQL trigger using moddatetime() extension |
| RLS — customers | Customers read/write only their own rows in favorites, enquiries, notifications, push_tokens |
| RLS — vendors | Vendors read/write only their own rows in vendors, vendor_* tables, enquiries (where vendor_id matches) |
| RLS — public read | Verified + active/trial vendors and their services/portfolio/packages/reviews are publicly readable |
| RLS — admin | Admin bypasses RLS via service role key in Edge Functions only |
| Unique payment | payments.razorpay_payment_id has a UNIQUE constraint to prevent duplicate payment processing |
| Soft delete | vendors.deleted_at is set instead of hard DELETE; all public queries filter WHERE deleted_at IS NULL |

### 6.4 Data Retention

| Data | Retention Policy |
|------|-----------------|
| Customer PII (phone, name) | Retained while account active; deleted within 30 days of account deletion request (DPDP compliance) |
| Vendor data | Retained indefinitely (soft deleted only) for audit trail and subscription history |
| Payment records | Retained for 7 years (Indian financial record-keeping requirement) |
| Notifications | Retained for 90 days; older rows purged by scheduled Edge Function |
| Push tokens | Purged on logout; stale tokens (no activity >90 days) purged by cron |

---

## 7. Constraints

### 7.1 Platform Constraints

| ID | Constraint |
|----|-----------|
| PC-01 | expo prebuild must be run before any native Android/iOS build; native folders are not version-controlled |
| PC-02 | metro.config.js must include cjs and mjs in sourceExts to resolve nanoid/non-secure |
| PC-03 | babel.config.js uses jsxImportSource: 'nativewind' in the preset; the nativewind/babel plugin must NOT be used (NativeWind v4 breaking change) |
| PC-04 | tailwind.config.js content paths must include all app/**/*.tsx and components/**/*.tsx files; missing paths cause NativeWind class names to not generate |
| PC-05 | app.json is the sole Expo config; app.config.js must not be introduced without migrating all existing fields |

### 7.2 Legal & Compliance

| ID | Constraint |
|----|-----------|
| LC-01 | A Privacy Policy page must be live at a public URL before Play Store submission |
| LC-02 | A Terms of Service page must be live at a public URL before Play Store submission |
| LC-03 | The Privacy Policy must disclose: phone number collection, location data, photo uploads, and any third-party data sharing (Razorpay, Cloudinary, MSG91) |
| LC-04 | Razorpay subscription terms and vendor cancellation/refund policy must be included in the Terms of Service |
| LC-05 | All WhatsApp Business template messages must be pre-registered with Meta via MSG91 DLT; unregistered templates will be rejected |
| LC-06 | Indian GST/PAN documentation must be submitted to Razorpay for KYC before processing live payments |

### 7.3 Business Rules

| ID | Rule |
|----|------|
| BR-01 | A vendor with is_verified = false or subscription_status IN ('expired', 'suspended') shall not appear in any customer-facing listing or search result |
| BR-02 | Premium vendors shall be sorted above Standard vendors; Standard above Basic in all listing and search results |
| BR-03 | Featured vendors (is_featured = true) shall appear on the Home screen; only Premium plan vendors are eligible for the is_featured flag |
| BR-04 | Trial subscription begins from the date the admin approves the vendor (is_verified = true); the clock does not start at registration |
| BR-05 | A vendor's subscription plan limits apply server-side; a Basic vendor receiving their 11th enquiry of the month shall receive an error response from the enquiry Edge Function |
| BR-06 | Once a vendor's category is set and the vendor is verified, the category field cannot be changed by the vendor; only an admin can modify it |
| BR-07 | The minimum starting price a vendor can set is Rs.1; the field must not accept zero or negative values |

